<F P=100> SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Afghanistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   100-Man Opposition Forces Switch to Government Side </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    100-Man Opposition Forces Switch to Government Side </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0104185694 Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network in Pashto 1530 
GMT 1 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0104185694 </F>
<F P=104>  Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Pashto </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In continuation of the Golboddin-Dostum militiamen 
coming over to the side of government in the country's northern 
regions, today 100-man armed group, led by Mohammad Nasim, 
joined the Islamic army's division 24 in Fariab province. 
  The military correspondent of Bakhtar Information Agency 
reports from Fariab province that since the start of clearing-up 
operation of the country's northern regions carried out by the 
Islamic army's forces and Mojahedin, thousands of militiamen 
have abandoned the Golboddin-Karmal-Dostum infamous triangle 
ranks and came over to the side of the Islamic army's forces and 
Mojahedin stationed in these regions. 
  The report adds that the mopping-up operation by the 
Mojahedin and the Islamic army has been continuing vigorously in 
Fariab province. The inhabitants and the Muslim people of 
Fariab province have been always earnestly cooperating with 
Mojahedin and the units of the Islamic army for the elimination 
of the last nests of communism in the country, and they 
sincerely discharge their Islamic duty. 

</TEXT>

